  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1941 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet features a framed photograph of the upper bodies and faces of a young smiling couple with a dog sitting between them. Her lips are painted. She is wearing a necklace and a kind of ornamented headdress with a white veil falling across her back. He is wearing an embroidered shirt and has curly hair. The dog is black. She is resting her right hand on the dog; he his left. Below, the film title is displayed in its Serbo-Croatian translation, (in the Russian original: ‘Конёк–Горбунок’, (Hunch back horse) – a ‘Soviet film fable’.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was directed by Александр Роу (Aleksandr Rou) and released in 1941.</ab>
